4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would propose an amendment to the
6 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, relating to Pike
7 County, to authorize the Judge of Probate of Pike
8 County to exercise equity jurisdiction concurrent with
9 that of the circuit court in cases originally filed in
10 the Probate Court of Pike County if the judge of
11 probate is a licensed attorney in the State of Alabama.
12
13
14 A BILL
15 TO BE ENTITLED
16 AN ACT
17
18 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
19 of 2022, relating to Pike County, to authorize the Judge of
20 Probate of Pike County to exercise equity jurisdiction
21 concurrent with certain circuit court cases if the judge of
22 probate is a licensed attorney in the State of Alabama.
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
24 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
25 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
26 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
27 The Judge of Probate of Pike County may exercise equity
28 jurisdiction concurrent with that of the circuit court in
Page 1

jurisdiction concurrent with that of the circuit court in
HB371 INTRODUCED
29 cases originally filed in the Probate Court of Pike County if
30 the judge of probate is a licensed attorney in the State of
31 Alabama. In any case subject to this amendment, the judge of
32 probate shall possess the power and authority of a circuit
33 court judge trying the case, and the case shall be treated in
34 all respects in the same manner as a case filed in circuit
35 court. The Alabama Rules of Civil Procedure shall apply in the
36 cases except as otherwise specifically provided by law. This
37 amendment is self-executing, but the Legislature may enact
38 additional laws to implement this amendment if needed.
39 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
40 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
41 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
42 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
43 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
44 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
45 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
46 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
47 language; and translate effective dates.
48 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
49 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
50 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
51 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
52 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
53 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
54 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
55 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
56 constitutional amendment:
